<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n18113j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n18" href="#n18113j">N18 (VI.B.8)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n18all.htm#n18113j"> 113(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cisium trap </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: CISIUM: a gig, a light open carriage with two wheels, adapted to carry two persons rapidly from place to place. It had a box or case, probably under the seat. The cisia were quickly drawn by mules. They were kept for hire at the stations along the great roads. The conductors of these hired gigs were called <i>cisiarii</i>, and were subject to penalties for careless or dangerous driving. </mm> </dd></dl>
